               <msContents>
                  <summary>Collection of protective prayers:&#xD;
I) Lǝfāfa ṣǝdǝq “Bandlet of Righteousness” (fols. 4r-20r)&#xD;
II) Mangada samāy “Journey to Heaven” (fols. 20r-27r)&#xD;
III) Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt “Teaching of Mysteries” (fols. 27v-38v)&#xD;
IV) Ṣalota bäräd Prayer against hail” (fols. 38v-41v)&#xD;
V) Ṣalota nädära, ʾAsmat-prayer against a disease called nädära which is the evil eye(fols. 41v-44r) (similar to Ms. Wellcome Institute, no. V,5, see S. STRELCYN, "Catalogue of Ethiopian manuscripts of the Wellcome Institute of the History of Medicine in London", BSOAS 35, 1, 1972], 27-55, here 31)&#xD;
VI) Ṣalota ba-ʾǝnta ḥǝmamä ʿaynätä säbʾ "Prayer Concerning the Desease of the Evil Eye of the People" (fols. 44r-47v)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additiones 1-7.</summary>
